generalComments.body: 1976Be56: E=27 MeV. Measured: \ensuremath{\gamma}(semi); \ensuremath{\gamma}\ensuremath{\gamma}(semi-semi); \ensuremath{\gamma}(\ensuremath{\theta}) \ensuremath{\theta}=30\ensuremath{^\circ}, 60\ensuremath{^\circ}, 90\ensuremath{^\circ}; ce(semi); excitation functions E(\ensuremath{\alpha})=22, 24, 27 MeV

1976De11: measured: \ensuremath{\gamma}(semi) (E(\ensuremath{\alpha})=28.5 MeV); \ensuremath{\gamma}\ensuremath{\gamma} (semi-semi) (E(\ensuremath{\alpha})= 30.5 MeV); \ensuremath{\gamma}(\ensuremath{\theta}) \ensuremath{\theta}=90\ensuremath{^\circ}, 112\ensuremath{^\circ}, 125\ensuremath{^\circ}, 135\ensuremath{^\circ}, 145\ensuremath{^\circ}, 156\ensuremath{^\circ} (E(\ensuremath{\alpha})=30.5 MeV); excitation functions E(\ensuremath{\alpha})=28.5, 33.5, 37.0, 40.0 MeV.
No isomeric level with T\ensuremath{_{\textnormal{1/2}}}\ensuremath{>}1 ns observed (1976De11)

Level schemes of 1976Be56 and 1976De11 are in agreement for levels below 3 MeV. However, above 3 MeV there is little agreement. Except for levels at 3056.7 and 3178.3, other energy levels given here are due to 1976Be56. 1976De11 have proposed the following levels above 3178, with depopulating transitions given in parenthesis: 3486.8(514.6), 3594.8(416.5), 3641.1(668.9), 3827.8(341.1,925.2), 3910.5(82.7,315.5,423.7,1007.9), 4224.2(396.4), 4283.1(372.6,455.2), 4468.7(185.6,558.2), 4630.9(162.2), 4986.5(355.6,703.5) \ensuremath{\gamma}\ensuremath{\gamma}-coincidences shown are also due to 1976Be56. Some of the levels proposed by 1976Be56 do not seem to be in disagreement with \ensuremath{\gamma}\ensuremath{\gamma} results of 1976De11.

Unless stated otherwise, E\ensuremath{\gamma}, I\ensuremath{\gamma}, \ensuremath{\gamma}(\ensuremath{\theta}), \ensuremath{\alpha}(K)exp values of 1976Be56 are given. For many levels branching ratios of 1976Be56 differ from 1976De11. These are given in comments.
From \ensuremath{\alpha}(K)exp, normalized to 696\ensuremath{\gamma} (E2). The \ensuremath{\alpha}(K)exp values given have been estimated by the evaluator from the plot given by 1976Be56.
